						COVID-19 Information					














What do you need to know about the novel coronavirus COVID-19?

The Ridgway School District is closely monitoring the latest developments on the 2019 novel coronavirus. 

New information is being released frequently and it is important that we all stay informed as updates are released from reliable sources. 

At this time, the risk to most Coloradans from the COVID-19 virus is low and we are confident the health care system in our state is prepared to promptly and effectively address any suspected cases and minimize the threat of potential disease spread.

We are committed to providing access to the latest information to keep our students, staff, parents, and community members safe. To learn more about the COVID-19 virus and to access the latest information, please visit:

 The Centers for Disease Control Website: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019- ncov/index.html 

 Ouray County Public Health Website: https://ouraycountyco.gov/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=308

 ​Colorado COVID-19 Case Summary: https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vRSxDeeJEaDxir0cCd9Sfji8ZPKzNaCPZnvRCbG63Oa1ztz4B4r7xG_wsoC9ucd_ei3--Pz7UD50yQD/pub

Spring Sport Information from CHSAA: https://chsaanow.com/2020-03-12/spring-sports-and-activities-suspended-until-april-6/

Fact Sheet from CDC in English: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/downloads/2019-ncov-factsheet.pdf

Fact Sheet from CDC in Spanish: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/downloads/2019-ncov-factsheet-sp.pdf

 Guidelines from CDC in English https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/downloads/sick-with-2019-nCoV-fact-sheet.pdf

Guidelines from CDC in Spanish https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/downloads/sick-with-2019-nCoV-fact-sheet-sp.pdf

Important Updates from Superintendent Susan Lacy.



